The "no-such-handle" error comes from the following code in transport.c in a few places.

```
pn_link_t *link = pni_handle_state(ssn, handle);

  if (!link) {
    return pn_do_error(transport, "amqp:invalid-field", "no such handle: %u", handle);
  }
```

Looks like proton is trying to send a message to a receiver on a link that was closed abruptly. The router will try to redeliver this message to another receiver. This error can be ignored in the context of what this test is trying to achieve.

